extends ../layouts/2col.pug

block append config
  - var pageTitle = 'Badge';
  - var pageSubtitle = 'Small count and labeling component';
  - var skipMenu = true;

block content
  .card
    .card-body
      h3 Example
      p Badges scale to match the size of the immediate parent element by using relative font sizing and <code>em</code> units. As of v5, badges no longer have focus or hover styles for links.

      h3 Headings

      .bd-example
        h1
          | Example heading
          span.badge.bg-secondary New
        h2
          | Example heading
          span.badge.bg-secondary New
        h3
          | Example heading
          span.badge.bg-secondary New
        h4
          | Example heading
          span.badge.bg-secondary New
        h5
          | Example heading
          span.badge.bg-secondary New
        h6
          | Example heading
          span.badge.bg-secondary New

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;h1&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge bg-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
          | &lt;h2&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge bg-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
          | &lt;h3&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge bg-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
          | &lt;h4&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge bg-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
          | &lt;h5&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge bg-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
          | &lt;h6&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge bg-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;

      h3 Buttons
      p Badges can be used as part of links or buttons to provide a counter.

      .bd-example
        button.btn.btn-primary(type='button')
          | Notifications
          span.badge.text-bg-secondary 4

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;button type='button' class="btn btn-primary"&gt;
          |   Notifications &lt;span class="badge text-bg-secondary"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;/button&gt;

      p Note that depending on how they are used, badges may be confusing for users of screen readers and similar assistive technologies. While the styling of badges provides a visual cue as to their purpose, these users will simply be presented with the content of the badge. Depending on the specific situation, these badges may seem like random additional words or numbers at the end of a sentence, link, or button.

      p Unless the context is clear (as with the “Notifications” example, where it is understood that the “4” is the number of notifications), consider including additional context with a visually hidden piece of additional text.

      h3 Positioned
      p Use utilities to modify a <code>.badge</code> and position it in the corner of a link or button.

      .bd-example
        button.btn.btn-primary.position-relative(type='button')
          | Inbox
          span.position-absolute.top-0.start-100.translate-middle.badge.rounded-pill.bg-danger
            | 99+
            span.visually-hidden unread messages

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;button type='button' class="btn btn-primary position-relative"&gt;
          |   Inbox
          |   &lt;span class="position-absolute top-0 start-100 translate-middle badge rounded-pill bg-danger"&gt;
          |     99+
          |     &lt;span class="visually-hidden"&gt;unread messages&lt;/span&gt;
          |   &lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;/button&gt;

      p You can also replace the .badge class with a few more utilities without a count for a more generic indicator.

      .bd-example
        button.btn.btn-primary.position-relative(type='button')
          | Profile
          span.position-absolute.top-0.start-100.translate-middle.p-2.bg-danger.border.border-light.rounded-circle
            span.visually-hidden New alerts

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;button type='button' class="btn btn-primary position-relative"&gt;
          |   Profile
          |   &lt;span class="position-absolute top-0 start-100 translate-middle p-2 bg-danger border border-light rounded-circle"&gt;
          |     &lt;span class="visually-hidden"&gt;New alerts&lt;/span&gt;
          |   &lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;/button&gt;

      h3 Background colors
      p Set a <code>background-color</code> with contrasting foreground <code>color</code> with our <code>.text-bg-{color}</code> helpers. Previously it was required to manually pair your choice of <code>.text-{color}</code> and <code>.bg-{color}</code> utilities for styling, which you still may use if you prefer.

      .bd-example
        span.badge.text-bg-primary Primary
        span.badge.text-bg-secondary Secondary
        span.badge.text-bg-success Success
        span.badge.text-bg-danger Danger
        span.badge.text-bg-warning Warning
        span.badge.text-bg-info Info
        span.badge.text-bg-light Light
        span.badge.text-bg-dark Dark

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;span class="badge text-bg-primary"&gt;Primary&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge text-bg-secondary"&gt;Secondary&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge text-bg-success"&gt;Success&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge text-bg-danger"&gt;Danger&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge text-bg-warning"&gt;Warning&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge text-bg-info"&gt;Info&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge text-bg-light"&gt;Light&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge text-bg-dark"&gt;Dark&lt;/span&gt;

      h3 Pill badges
      p Use the <code>.rounded-pill</code> utility class to make badges more rounded with a larger <code>border-radius</code>.

      .bd-example
        span.badge.rounded-pill.text-bg-primary Primary
        span.badge.rounded-pill.text-bg-secondary Secondary
        span.badge.rounded-pill.text-bg-success Success
        span.badge.rounded-pill.text-bg-danger Danger
        span.badge.rounded-pill.text-bg-warning Warning
        span.badge.rounded-pill.text-bg-info Info
        span.badge.rounded-pill.text-bg-light Light
        span.badge.rounded-pill.text-bg-dark Dark

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;span class="badge rounded-pill text-bg-primary"&gt;Primary&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge rounded-pill text-bg-secondary"&gt;Secondary&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge rounded-pill text-bg-success"&gt;Success&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge rounded-pill text-bg-danger"&gt;Danger&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge rounded-pill text-bg-warning"&gt;Warning&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge rounded-pill text-bg-info"&gt;Info&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge rounded-pill text-bg-light"&gt;Light&lt;/span&gt;
          | &lt;span class="badge rounded-pill text-bg-dark"&gt;Dark&lt;/span&gt;
